comment_regular_data.body:
@bfredl 
I would like to test this new event.
I understand that top can be shrunk by winbar, but I would like to have values other than top greater than 1 (i.e., a grid where, for example, grid is 2 and top, bottom, left, and right are all 1). Is it possible to create such a grid?

@Kethku thx for the info :D 

@bfredl 
Additional requests related to this PR are possible.
While goneovim implements smooth horizontal scrolling using the touchpad, there is a possibility that some users may not want line numbers and other parts(e.g. git change sign) of the content area to move when scrolling horizontally. In goneovim, line number cells are detected by their highlight names and are kept in place during smooth horizontal scrolling.  [See](https://github.com/akiyosi/goneovim/blob/6f5e78758ca189cc7ac3c64e90a739980d58a807/editor/window.go#L2309-L2311)
However, this method does not work well with inactive or floating windows, since such windows cannot identify line number cells by their highlight names.
I am not sure if it is good design to approach such issues directly with the win_viewport_margins event, but is it something to consider?
